        "subject": "LU-521 make LST support variable page size",
        "message": "LU-521 make LST support variable page size\n\nLNet selftest can't support variable page size because it sends\nnumber of pages over the wire.\nWe have to change wire format to fix this but it will have compatibility\nissue, so this patch also implemented \"session version\" for LST to\nresolve compatibility issue, only new version LST can understand new\nbulk RPC format, although new LST nodes still can communicate with old\nLST nodes.  This feature requires all nodes in the cluster are running\nwith the same session version, which means if there are some nodes are\nrunning old version LST, those nodes with new LST also have to run with\ncompatible old version by setting env variable LST_VERSION.\nPlease see the Jira ticket (LU-521) for more details.\n\nChange-Id: I889b4023995ab2fde28b8de79977379e2f291cd0\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
